4, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.244511585124028e-62, \"text\": \"BMI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Critics\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"the term\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2290}, {\"ngram\": \"a societal judgment\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2325}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2348}, {\"ngram\": \"arbitrary categories\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"misconceptions\", \"from\": 2391, \"to\": 2405}, {\"ngram\": \"body weight\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even with all thebacklash against \\\"fat-shaming,\\\"weight stigma against the seriously overweight or those who have obesity remains deep-rooted,according to research.\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2588, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all thebacklash\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2450}, {\"ngram\": \"fat-shaming,\\\"weight stigma\", \"from\": 2460, \"to\": 2486}, {\"ngram\": \"the seriously overweight\", \"from\": 2495, \"to\": 2519}, {\"ngram\": \"obesity\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2545}, {\"ngram\": \"research\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2587}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Related articleHow to think like an Olympian and develop a winner's brain A BMI measurement can be flat wrong in some cases, Thomas Wadden, a professor of psychology at the Perelman School of Medicine at the University of Pennsylvania,told CNN in an earlier interview.\", \"from\": 2590, \"to\": 2859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2626, \"end\": 2634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999998658495, \"rank\": 6.923800846710207e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2667, \"end\": 2670, \"title\"